{:cascade/id "ants-forward-pattern-cascade-v0"
 :cascade/title "The Ant Pattern Cascade"
 :cascade/subtitle "Five inherited patterns, read as a cascade — and what the reading exposes"
 :cascade/psi
 "An ant brain characterised as a pattern cascade: one given at the floor, a derivation of contended parameters above it, and a drive that cannot settle. The ants already hold the one thing the futon7a cascade declares a hole — an external rubric. They eat."

 :cascade/generated
 "Composed 2026-07-16 by claude-2 from futon3/library/ants/*.flexiarg (5 patterns, IF/HOWEVER/THEN/BECAUSE/NEXT-STEPS + @aif-delta + @status + @sigils). Wires read off slot-adjacency (one pattern's THEN feeding another's IF) AND off @aif-delta key contention (two patterns writing the same config key). Style follows futon7a lab/pattern-cascade/cascade.edn. Bottom-to-top: it is a Hasse diagram of a join-semilattice, not a proof tree — joins go up."

 :cascade/epistemic-note
 "THE EPISTEMIC AXIS IS NOT THE ONE futon7a USES. There, attested = a war-room ruling.
  Here, every flexiarg carries @status[ready] with evidence pointing at Futon2 goldens —
  but those goldens attest that the pattern FAITHFULLY DESCRIBES THE CODE, not that it
  IMPROVES FORAGING. So:
    :attested     = 'this describes what Futon2 does'   (evidence: goldens)
    :hypothetical = 'this helps the ant forage'         (NO evidence; see :cascade/gate)
  Reading @status[ready] as 'the pattern works' is the category error this cascade exists
  to prevent."

 :cascade/gate
 {:ran "2026-07-16, scripts/pattern_authority_gate.clj, 20 paired seeds x 300 ticks"
  :verdict "AUTHORITY FAIL — no real pattern differed from `off` by held-out yield sign test at any lambda in {0.1,0.5,1.0}"
  :controls "SOUND. sham (:cyber/baseline) tied `off` exactly on every seed at every lambda, matching full event traces; lambda=0 tied for all five ids."
  :scope-limit
  "CRUCIAL: the gate set `:cyber-pattern {:id ...}` DIRECTLY. It did NOT call
   `cyber/attach-config`, so it never merged the @aif-delta into :aif-config. The patterns
   have TWO channels and only one was tested:
     channel 1  @aif-delta -> :aif-config   (via attach-config, keyword path,
                `cyber.clj:213` = `(update :aif-config merge-deep (:aif-delta config))`)
                -- the patterns' DECLARED PARAMETERS.  ** NEVER TESTED **
     channel 2  pattern_efe.clj hard-coded risk/info-gain (via :id + lambda.pattern)
                -- a SEPARATE reimplementation.  ** TESTED, FAILED **
   So the verdict reads: 'the hard-coded EFE terms do not move the ant.' It does NOT read
   'the design patterns do not move the ant.' Channel 1 is untested and is the cascade's
   first live question."
  :readme-nuance
  "README-xeno-loop §0 says `config->aif-delta` merges ONLY :precision (:tau,:Pi-o). TRUE —
   but that is `apply-external-config`, the `{:config ...}` path used by the old futon5
   cyberant configs. The FLEXIARG path (`attach-config`, keyword id) merges the WHOLE delta.
   §0's inertness critique does not transfer to the library patterns."}

 :cascade/boxes
 [;; ---- the floor: the given ----
  {:id "b0" :ns "ants" :epistemic :attested :role :foundation
   :pattern "ants/baseline-cyber-ant" :title "Baseline Cyber-AIF Ant"
   :sigils "🗿/三 🌝/四" :status :draft
   :delta {} ;; literally empty: "no overrides; identical behavior to :aif species"
   :gist "The unpatterned ant. Its @aif-delta is EMPTY — it is the identity element of the pattern algebra."
   :note "FREE: the only box with no incoming wire. The scaffold. And note what the propagator theory says about the identity: all cycles length 1 = odd = NO fixed point. The unpatterned ant is the random walk."}

  ;; ---- the derivation: four parameter patterns ----
  {:id "hp" :ns "ants" :epistemic :attested :role :precision
   :pattern "ants/hunger-precision-coupling" :title "Hunger ↔ Precision Coupling"
   :sigils "💫/六 👴/万" :status :ready
   :delta {:precision {:need-gain 0.7 :dhdt-gain 0.9 :tau-survival-gain 0.6}
           :efe {:lambda {:survival 1.4}}}
   :gist "Hungrier ants lower tau; home safety lifts it; deficit reserves subtract."
   :role-note "The tau SOURCE. Everything downstream contends with it."}

  {:id "cr" :ns "ants" :epistemic :attested :role :discipline
   :pattern "ants/cargo-return-discipline" :title "Cargo Return Discipline"
   :sigils "📐/归" :status :ready
   :delta {:modes {:cargo-high 0.55}
           :precision {:tau-cap 1.2}
           :actions {:return {:cargo-thresh 0.1 :empty-home-pen 1.1}}}
   :gist "Penalise :return until a deposit fires; cap tau so the agent exploits completion."
   :role-note "Writes tau (cap) and :return cost. The only pattern touching :modes."}

  {:id "pt" :ns "ants" :epistemic :attested :role :signalling
   :pattern "ants/pheromone-trail-tuner" :title "Adaptive Trail Tuner"
   :sigils "➰/去" :status :ready
   :delta {:precision {:pher-scale 1.3 :trail-grad-scale 1.2}
           :efe {:lambda {:info 0.5}}
           :actions {:pheromone {:base-cost 0.008 :hunger-mult 0.08}}}
   :gist "Adapt signalling to novelty and resource pressure."
   :role-note "Writes :efe :lambda :info = 0.5. See :cascade/contentions."}

  {:id "ws" :ns "ants" :epistemic :attested :role :exploration
   :pattern "ants/white-space-scout" :title "White-Space Scout"
   :sigils "🌹/刊 👎/二" :status :ready
   :delta {:precision {:food-scale 1.8 :novelty-scale 1.4 :tau-floor 0.12}
           :efe {:lambda {:info 0.6 :ambiguity 0.4}}}
   :gist "White space implies scout stance: raise :forage, tolerate uncertainty."
   :role-note "Writes :efe :lambda :info = 0.6. DIRECTLY CONTENDS with pt."}

  ;; ---- the frontier ----
  {:id "hc" :ns "forward-model" :epistemic :hypothetical :role :frontier
   :pattern "forward-model/food-cache-relay" :title "Food-Cache Relay"
   :extends "cr"
   :gist "IF :carrying and :made-progress-homeward HOWEVER :still-far-from-home THEN :drop and :forage BECAUSE :relay-beats-the-round-trip. Joe 2026-07-16, refined: the naive version (drop when far) is a food SINK — nothing ratchets it home."
   :blocked-by "hole-vocab"
   :note "The FIRST pattern that would add a CAPABILITY rather than a constraint. All five inherited patterns only reweight the four fixed actions."}

  {:id "hg" :ns "forward-model" :epistemic :hypothetical :role :loop
   :pattern "forward-model/graduate-by-yield" :title "Graduate By Yield"
   :gist "A pattern becomes attested-as-helpful only by passing the authority gate on held-out boards. Differs, not beats: a pattern that reliably harms is still a live actuator."}

  {:id "hm" :ns "forward-model" :epistemic :hypothetical :role :apex
   :pattern "forward-model/the-ant-brain-is-a-pattern-cascade" :title "The Ant Brain Is A Pattern Cascade"
   :gist "The join. Scaffold (FREE) + derivation (wires) + a drive that cannot settle (the holes) — Figure 8's anatomy, in an agent."}]

