 :cascade/contentions
 [{:key [:efe :lambda :info] :writers {"pt" 0.5 "ws" 0.6}
   :severity :unsat
   :why "Two patterns demand different values of ONE key. `merge-deep` makes the result depend on attachment order, which is not a property of either pattern. Only one pattern is active at a time today (`:pattern/active` is singular), so they never collide — the conflict is INVISIBLE until you compose. A cascade composes. This is the constraint `g[k] = 0.5 AND g[k] = 0.6`: unsatisfiable."}
  {:key [:precision "tau-family"] :writers {"hp" ":need-gain/:dhdt-gain/:tau-survival-gain" "cr" ":tau-cap" "ws" ":tau-floor"}
   :severity :contended
   :why "Three patterns shape tau through DIFFERENT keys, so merge-deep does not detect the contention — but they are arguing about one quantity. cr caps it, ws floors it, hp drives it. Whether cap > floor is never checked."}
  {:key [:actions :return] :writers {"cr" ":cargo-thresh/:empty-home-pen" "ws" "G-lowering (prose only, no delta key)"}
   :severity :latent
   :why "ws's THEN says 'lower G for :return' but its @aif-delta has NO :actions key. The behaviour is in prose, not in the delta. Channel 1 cannot express it; only the hard-coded pattern_efe can — and that channel just failed the gate."}]

 :cascade/joins
 [{:of ["hp" "cr"] :pattern "tau-is-a-shared-resource" :gist "hunger drives tau, discipline caps it — the join is a tau budget nobody owns."}
  {:of ["pt" "ws"] :pattern "novelty-is-double-counted" :gist "both read novelty and both price :info. The join is a single exploration drive written twice."}
  {:of ["cr" "hc"] :pattern "avoid-the-round-trip" :gist "cargo discipline and cache relay are the same pattern at two strengths: stop thrashing (reweight) vs stop travelling (new action)."}]

